add_reactions.reason: if you want to have polls or commands that need conformation this is needed, also if you allow the bot to write in a channel, this is one that should be automatically set too

read_messages.reason: if you want the bot to be able to be invoked in that channel, this is needed to be set, or if you want the bot to parse the channel this is needed to be set, also if you allow the bot to write in a channel, this is one that should be automatically set too.

send_messages.reason: If you want a command to answer with anything in that channel this is needed to be set, also if you allow the bot to write in a channel, this is one that should be automatically set too

manage_messages.reason: This is needed for the bot to clean up his own messages after some time but also to clean away the invokation message, so not to fill the channel with invokation messages, also if you allow the bot to write in a channel, this is one that should be automatically set too

embed_links.reason: many embeds use non dynamic Thumbnails and these are implemented via links, also you can create short hyperlink links via the bot

attach_files.reason: if an embed uses a dynamically created image, this is neeeded to be set as this image works by being an attachment

read_message_history.reason: if you ever want to scrape all messages in that channel and archive them.

change_nickname.reason: mandatory permission, means only that the bot can change its own permissions

manage_roles.reason: Needed for future Subscriber mechanic and temp Roles
